# Python Linter Rule - Ruff

## Linter Information
- Use the Ruff linter for Python code
- Version: latest
- Configuration in pyproject.toml

## When to Trigger
- **ALWAYS run after any Python file edit is completed**
- Run before committing code
- Run when checking code quality

## How to Run
- Run with: `uv run ruff check --fix .`
- Always use the --fix parameter to automatically fix issues when possible
- For specific files: `uv run ruff check --fix path/to/file.py`

## Actions
- Run linter after making any code changes
- Fix all linter issues before committing
- Respect existing configuration in pyproject.toml
- For severe issues that can't be auto-fixed, describe the problem and suggest solutions
